Then, let us divide both sides by 2.30% to cancel out the coefficient of portfolio weight. This is shown as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
{\dfrac{\text{2.30\%PW}}{\text{2.30\%}}}&=\dfrac{\text{1.05\%}}{\text{2.30\%}}\\
{\textbf{PW}}&={\textbf{45.65\%}}
\end{aligned}$$

**The portfolio weight of Stock X is 45.65%.**
